cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and multi-document summarization. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the task of summarization involves retrieving relevant information from multiple documents. Additionally, the use of sentence embeddings and graph-based models suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of data-driven methods and neural networks suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
